<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<aiml>

<!-- START PRACTICE -->
<category>
  <pattern>PRACTICE MODE</pattern>
  <template>
    <think>
      <set name="mode">practice</set>
      <set name="scenario">refund</set>
    </think>

    🎯 Scenario 1:

    A user says:
    "I want a refund but your system is not working."

    👉 Write how a GOOD chatbot should respond.
  </template>
</category>

<!-- USER RESPONSE EVALUATION -->
<category>
  <pattern>*</pattern>
  <that>🎯 Scenario 1*</that>
  <template>

    <think><set name="last_answer"><star/></set></think>

    👍 Good attempt.

    🧠 Feedback:
    - Did you acknowledge the problem?
    - Did you guide the user?
    - Did you ask for required info?

    💡 Ideal response:
    "I’m sorry you're facing this issue. Can you share your order ID so I can help process your refund?"

    Say NEXT PRACTICE.
  </template>
</category>

<!-- NEXT SCENARIO -->
<category>
  <pattern>NEXT PRACTICE</pattern>
  <template>
    <think><set name="scenario">login</set></think>

    🎯 Scenario 2:

    User says:
    "I can't login to my account"

    👉 Write the best chatbot response.
  </template>
</category>

<!-- SECOND EVALUATION -->
<category>
  <pattern>*</pattern>
  <that>🎯 Scenario 2*</that>
  <template>

    👍 Nice try.

    🧠 Feedback:
    - Did you show empathy?
    - Did you guide next step?
    - Did you avoid robotic tone?

    💡 Ideal:
    "I'm sorry you're having trouble logging in. Try resetting your password or I can help you recover your account."

    Say COACH MODE for deeper feedback.
  </template>
</category>

</aiml>